description: From Middle English overberen; equivalent to over- +‎ bear.

verbs.description: overbear (third-person singular simple present overbears, present participle overbearing, simple past overbore, past participle overborne)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To push through by physical weight or strength; to overwhelm, overcome. [from 16th c.]
(transitive) To prevail over; to dominate, overpower; to oppress. [from 16th c.]
(intransitive) To produce an overabundance of fruit. [from 18th c.]
